This paper discusses the ethical foundations of fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the issues of learning and randomization, which are relevant to the categories of emerging technologies (cs.ET) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper provides a critique of existing definitions of fairness, which could be relevant to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
